  <p>
    ISJ's Christmas Concert lit up the school campus this December in a performance that showcased the extraordinary range of talent across the student body. The evening, beautifully brought together by music teacher Ms Grace Wang, was a reminder of just how much heart and skill the students at ISJ possess.
  </p>

  <h2>Music from Glockenspiel to Coldplay</h2>

  <p>
    The concert opened with an ensemble, with students performing a gorgeous glockenspiel arrangement of Ophelia Wilde, a piece that drew appreciative murmurs from the audience. As the evening progressed, the ISJ School Choir took centre stage, filling the campus with warm harmonies and festive spirit.
  </p>

  <p>
    Modern favourites also featured prominently. A performance of Coldplay's A Sky Full of Stars was a particular highlight, bringing the audience to their feet and capturing the celebratory mood of the night.
  </p>

  <h2>Dance, Ballet, and Special Performances</h2>

  <p>
    Between musical sets, the school's Ballet Club and K-Pop Dance Club delivered special interludes that delighted families and staff alike. The variety of performances underlined the breadth of the arts provision at ISJ, and the confidence and poise the students brought to the stage was impressive.
  </p>

  <h2>Families and Community</h2>

  <p>
    The school campus was filled not only with music but with the warmth of the ISJ community. Families came together to support their children and to celebrate the end of a busy and rewarding term. It was an evening of joy, pride, and togetherness.
  </p>

  <p>
    A huge well done to every student who performed, and to Ms Grace Wang for her dedication in preparing such a memorable show.
  </p>

</ArticleLayout>
